What a revelation!! I thought that site # 20 was in mothballs!<br><br>
Doc Spatz, you are right. People who are new to this site really should read more of the other threads. Especially those who enter this site with the intention of calling vile names. I thank any who have made mention of their appreciation for our service and our answering the &quot;call&quot;. But, I do not hesitate to add that if accepting  kind words requires agreement with the way Doc Spatz has been characterized, then I politely decline.<br><br>
The days of &quot;pigs&quot;, &quot;cowards&quot;, and &quot;effete,impudent snobs&quot; are over - thankfully. <br><br>
Those who engage in namecalling or who encourage others to not communicate with those with divergent views lose my respect immediately.<br><br>
There a common thread that has come to the surface on this site after many months of dialogue. That is this: guys like myself, Doc Del, Art, Gerry, Chet, Ratliff, and Spatz don't EVER want to see another fiasco like Vietnam!!!!<br><br>
Namecalling, and mischaracterizations lead to a lack of communication and distrust. Intractability and the worn out rhetoric will never provide any solutions.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


